PRIVACY POLICY
Last updated: 19.02.2024
1. WHO WE ARE
1.1. We are Hot Siberians LTD, a company established and operating under the legislation of Cyprus (reg. number: HE 422690), with its registered office at 155, Archiepiskopou Makariou III, 3026, Limassol, Cyprus ("we", "our", "us" or "COMPANY").
1.2. This Privacy Policy sets out how we collect and use your personal information when you use the Website, the Game and related services, offered by the COMPANY on the Website (for the purposes of this Privacy Policy all the above mentioned shall be collectively referred as the “Game” unless the context otherwise requires) and the choices available to you in connection with our use of your personal information (the "Privacy Policy").
1.3. It is reminded that information collected via the Game is used by the COMPANY, which is responsible for its processing.
2. WE AS DATA CONTROLLER
2.1. By using our Services you agree to our Privacy Policy.
2.2. We as Data Controller does not and will not process any special categories of personal data and ("sensitive data").
3. SCOPE OF THIS PRIVACY POLICY
3.1. This Privacy Policy explains how your Information is collected, used, and disclosed by Hot Siberians Ltd. ("we" or "us"). This Privacy Policy applies to all users of our mobile
games, including those using games on iOS, Android and other mobile devices.
4. INFORMATION WE COLLECT ABOUT YOU
4.1. We do not collect personal information from users of our games, except for statistical information necessary to improve the gaming experience and analyze gaming trends.
We may collect the following categories of statistical information:
1. Information about interactions with game elements, including, but not limited to, in-game actions, play time, levels, etc.
2. Aggregate statistics on the use of our games that are not associated with specific users.
4.2. Here you can find more about the information collected:
Purchase of goods/services. When you make a purchase, we provide you with third party services to complete your purchase, and your payment information (such as credit/debit card, billing information, and shipping address) is not collected by us.
Customer requests. When you contact us through one of our customer service teams or customer support centers, we may have access to your previous correspondence with us, or your contact information.
5. PURPOSES OF USING INFORMATION
5.1. Use of technical and usage information. We use technical and usage information to improve our design, functionality and content and to enable us to personalize your experience with our content and offerings.
We use this information to:
1. provide, develop, support, personalize, protect and improve our products, applications, services and video games, and operate our business,
2. to perform analytics, including analyzing and reporting usage and performance,
3. to protect, detect and prevent fraud and other illegal activities,
4. to create aggregate data about groups or categories of our users
5.2. The information we collect is used solely to improve the quality of our games, analyze gaming trends, and ensure a safe gaming experience. We do not collect or share this information with third parties without your consent.
6. COOKIES AND OTHER TECHNOLOGIES
6.1. We may use “cookies” and other technologies to collect information about your interactions with our games and to optimize your experience. You can manage your cookie preferences in your device or browser settings.
7. INTERNATIONAL TRANSFERS
7.1. We work internationally, collecting statistical information from various countries. Please note that the information we collect does not contain personal information and is only anonymous statistical data.
7.2. Because we operate outside the European Economic Area (EEA), we recognize that data protection and privacy regulations may vary from country to country and may not provide the same level of protection as in the EEA.
7.3. Where your information is transferred to members of our group or third parties outside the EEA, we will take appropriate measures to ensure that your data is adequately protected.
This may include the use of standard contractual clauses approved by the European Commission or other means such as Privacy Shield, BCR, etc.
8. RETENTION PERIODS
8.1. We do not collect personal information and therefore have no need to store any personal data. However, we retain anonymous statistical data for the period necessary to fulfill the purposes for which the data was collected. This period is determined in accordance with the goals of improving the quality of our games, analyzing gaming trends and ensuring the safety of the gaming experience.
8.2. You can delete your data by simply deleting it from your account. Given that no personal information is collected, this means the removal of statistical data associated with your account.
8.3. If you wish to delete your account and all data associated with it, you can request this by contacting our Customer Service. Please note that deleting an account will also delete all statistics associated with it.
8.4. We may delete your account or certain information you have posted in accordance with the terms of the EULA.
9. YOUR CALIFORNIA PRIVACY RIGHTS
9.1. In accordance with the California Consumer Privacy Act of 2018 ("CCPA"), we at Hot Siberians LTD want to provide California residents with additional information about the collection and use of their personal information. Please note that we do not collect personal data, only anonymous statistical information in our mobile games.
9.2. Categories of information collected:
We collect only the following categories of information, which cannot be used to identify specific users:
1. Usage Data: Information about your in-game activities, such as play time, play levels, and interactions with game elements.
9.3. Purposes of using information:
The information we collect is used solely for the following purposes:
1. Improving the quality of our games and optimizing the gameplay.
2. Analyze gaming trends and provide statistical data for our internal purposes.
3. Ensuring the security and stable operation of our games.
We do not sell, rent, or share your information with third parties without your consent. 9.4. Your rights under the CCPA:
California residents have certain rights regarding their personal information under the CCPA. These rights include:
1. The right to request a copy of the information we have collected about you.
2. The right to delete your personal information collected by us.
3. The right to opt-out of the sale of your personal information (although we do not sell your information).
If you would like to exercise your rights or have any questions or queries regarding our Privacy Policy, please contact us using the contact information provided.
10. SECURITY MEASURES
10.1. We make every reasonable effort to protect the statistical information we collect from unauthorized access, use or disclosure. We use modern technologies and procedures to ensure data security.
11. CHANGES TO THIS POLICY
11.1. From time to time, we may change and/or update this Privacy Policy. If this Privacy Policy changes in any way, we will post an updated version on this page. We recommend you regularly review this page to ensure that you are always aware of our information practices and any changes to them.
12. CONTACT US
12.1. If you have any questions, please send your enquiries to our Support Service at
hotsiberians@gmail.com
. Please quote this Privacy Policy so we can deal with your enquiry efficiently. We will aim to respond to you within 30 days from receipt of your request.
12.2. All correspondence received by us from you (electronic enquiries) is classified as restricted-access information and may not be disclosed without your written consent. The personal data and other information about you may not be used without your consent for any purpose other than for responding to the enquiry, except as expressly provided by law.
We are committed to ensuring transparency and data protection for all users of our games. If you have any questions or concerns regarding our Privacy Policy, please contact us using the contact information provided.
